NEXT VERSION

v1.27.0 2025.04.29

- PONRTSYS-14752: Implement link status reporting for pon0 netdev
- PONRTSYS-14777: Create "altname" for pon0 interface
  + Check for the attribute "intel,altname" in the pon_eth node
- PONRTSYS-13291: OMCI ME 344/454 - (Enhanced) TC PMHD - Feature implementation
  + Enhancements in the driver functionality to allow LODS specific mbox message
    PONFW_TWDM_LODS_COUNTERS_CMD_ID for counter retrieval in XG(S)-PON mode in
    addition to NG-PON2 mode.

v1.26.1 2025.03.13

- PONRTSYS-14680: Prevent transmission if not in O5 state

v1.26.0 2025.02.03

- PONRTSYS-14349: Import FW message interface 4.0 header files

v1.25.2 2024.08.29

- PONRTSYS-14333: Active Ethernet mode kernel crash
  + Request "wanss" reset as shared reset, to ensure it is kept deasserted also
    when the xpcs driver is trying to toggle it.
- PONRTSYS-13996: UDP speedtest setup-cleanup repeated iterations lead to RTNETLINK error
  + extend the scan for gem across all active p-mappers while adding the gem to
    a p-mapper thereby preventing shifting of ownership (from DPM's point of
    view) to another p-mapper as new p-mappers get added which use same gem.
  + while destructing a p-mapper move ownership (from DPM's point of view) of
    any potentially shared gem to next available p-mapper which references it.
- PONRTSYS-14159: [NG-PON2] T-CONT net_devices associated with alloc-IDs greater than 4095 cannot be created
  + XGEM Port-ID also corrected for XG-PON1 case valid range begins at 1023 and not at 1021!
- PONRTSYS-14160: [NG-PON2] GEM net_devices associated with XGEM Port-IDs greater than 4095 cannot be created

v1.25.1 2024.07.12

- PONRTSYS-14139: [TPZ] Adapt pon_mbox-driver for Kernel 6.6
  + Allow to compile mbox driver (CONFIG_PON_MBOX_DRV) against newer kernel
- PONRTSYS-12980: LGM-C FW selection added
- PONRTSYS-14157: invert the input selector bit of loop timing pll for LGM-C
- PONRTSYS-14147: Soc specifics added to pon_soc_func
  + pon_soc_func renamed to pon_soc_data
  + Soc specific HW version override added, used for LGM-C
  + Soc specific HW version for the firmware added, used for LGM-C
  + HW IDs in PONFW_HW_VERSION_CMD_ID updated and supported

v1.25.0 2024.05.15

- PONRTSYS-13835: new FW-SAS 26, changes for LGM-C
  + additional padding function
  + loop timing modes removed
  + TIB interop bit removed

v1.24.1 2024.04.09

- PONRTSYS-13043: Bringup or port datapath components for PRX to kernel 5.15
  + ndo_bridge_getlink/setlink callbacks in net_device_ops were removed in
    kernel 4.14 release and not because of LGM.
    Fix the checks to use the kernel version instead of SoC type.
  + Allow the "sfp" link in device-tree to point to an "sff,sfp" node
    in addition to pointing directly to the i2c bus.
    This allows to prepare the device-tree to optionally use an Ethernet or
    AON SFP for the WAN port.

